<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0779 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Danish Institute of Forest Technology has been asked by the Ministryof Energy to evaluate the experiences gained in Skaane (Sweden) in relationto large scale cultivation of willow for the production of wood fuels.The economic factors were examined in relation to the plantations, harvestingand production costs, and the balance of production for arable and forestylands were studied, and illustrated by tables. The conclusion was thatit would be difficult to include large-scale production of wood fuelson a mini-rotation basis in Danish energy planning because of the presentdominance of natural gas projects. It would also involve changes in agricultureand forestry legislation. (AB).</TEXT></DOC>